content: I earn around $4,500 per month, and it's a fixed salary. My fixed expenses include rent, utilities, groceries, transportation, and minimum debt payments, which add up to around $3,500. I have a credit card debt of $2,000 with an interest rate of 18%, and a student loan of $30,000 with an interest rate of 6%. I'm trying to save for an emergency fund and eventually want to start planning for retirement. I currently have $1,000 in savings.
